%N A396671 Number of distinct tilings of an L-tromino of order n by elementary L-trominoes.
%C A396671 The L-tromino, also known as the chair, is a rep-tile.
%C A396671 The elementary L-tromino consists of three unit squares joined edge-to-edge to form an L-shape.
%C A396671 An L-tromino of order n is a scaled copy of the elementary L-tromino in which each square has side length n, where n is a positive integer.
